  DEPLOYMENT SEQUENCE (do in exact order):                                                                                                          
  1. Check HF Space webhooks alive: curl -s -X POST "https://lbjlincoln-nomos-rag-engine.hf.space/webhook/rag-multi-index-v3" -H "Content-Type:     
  application/json" -d '{"query":"test"}'                                                                                                           
  2. If HF Space dead → fix entrypoint.sh activation first (see scripts/ci_full_setup.py for reference)                                             
  3. If HF Space alive → deploy HF pipelines:                                                                                                       
     bash scripts/deploy-overnight.sh                                                                                                               
  4. Start Codespace rag-tests:                                                                                                                     
     gh codespace start --codespace nomos-rag-tests-5g6g5q9vjjwjf5g4                                                                                
     gh codespace ssh --codespace nomos-rag-tests-5g6g5q9vjjwjf5g4 -- 'cd /workspaces/rag-tests && bash scripts/deploy-codespace.sh'                
  5. Start Codespace data-ingestion (create if needed):                                                                                             
     gh codespace create --repo LBJLincoln/rag-data-ingestion --machine basicLinux32gb                                                              
  6. On each Codespace, after n8n up:                                                                                                               
     source .env.local && nohup python3 eval/run-eval-parallel.py --dataset phase-2 --all-parallel --workers 4 --batch-size 5 --force --early-stop  
  15 --label "overnight-cs" > /tmp/overnight.log 2>&1 &                                                                                             
  7. Back on VM: bash scripts/deploy-overnight.sh --status                                                                                          
  8. Verify all PIDs alive → safe to close terminal                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                    
  IF USER WANTS DIFFERENT OPENROUTER KEYS:                                                                                                          
  - Key 1: already in .env.local (HF Space uses this)                                                                                               
  - Key 2: export OPENROUTER_API_KEY=<new_key> in Codespace 1 .env.local                                                                            
  - Key 3: export OPENROUTER_API_KEY=<new_key> in Codespace 2 .env.local                                                                            
  Each key gets its own 20 req/min limit → 60 req/min total                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                    
  EVERYTHING RUNS AS nohup — survives terminal close, SSH disconnect, Claude Code exit.                                                             
  Auto-push commits every 15 minutes. Watchdog checks every 5 minutes.                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                    
  AFTER DEPLOYMENT: update session-state.md with all PIDs and then safe to exit.
